    <!-- How We Tested -->
    <section>
      <h2>How We Tested These Pain Relief Gummies</h2>

      <div class="tested-box">
        <h3>Our Testing Methodology</h3>
        <p>Our evaluation process was designed to go beyond marketing claims and provide genuine, evidence-based guidance for consumers seeking natural anti-inflammatory support.</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Procurement:</strong> Every product was purchased at full retail price from Amazon, Whole Foods, or the brand's direct website. We accepted no free samples, sponsorships, or early-access products. Our editorial independence is non-negotiable.</li>
          <li><strong>Ingredient Verification:</strong> Each formula was compared against published clinical research on PubMed. We evaluated whether curcumin dosages matched those used in peer-reviewed anti-inflammatory studies (typically 500-1,500mg daily) and whether bioavailability enhancement was included.</li>
          <li><strong>Third-Party Testing:</strong> We verified all testing claims by checking certification databases (USP, NSF, Informed Sport) directly. We also assessed heavy metal testing protocols, which is particularly important for turmeric products due to documented contamination concerns in the supply chain.</li>
          <li><strong>6-Week Testing Panel:</strong> A panel of 15 adults (ages 30-68) with self-reported joint discomfort tested each product for six consecutive weeks. Participants reported joint stiffness, comfort during daily activities, post-exercise recovery, and any side effects using standardized questionnaires.</li>
          <li><strong>Bioavailability Assessment:</strong> We compared absorption technologies (BioPerine, micellar formulations, C3 Complex, supercritical extraction) based on published pharmacokinetic data to determine which products deliver the most curcumin to systemic circulation.</li>
          <li><strong>Taste, Texture, and Value:</strong> Every product was scored on flavor, texture, aftertaste, and overall enjoyment. Total cost was divided by servings and weighed against ingredient quality to determine true per-serving value.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>Products were scored on a weighted scale: Ingredient Quality & Dosing (30%), Bioavailability (20%), Real-World Effectiveness (25%), Third-Party Testing (15%), and Value (10%). The rankings above reflect these composite scores.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

